<section>
	<h3>Game on</h3>
	<p>Let's give our page a <a href="/helloworld/tron/">retro, high-tech feel</a> inspired by Tron.</p>
	<ol>
		<li>Create a new stylesheet named <code>tron_style.css</code>.</li>
		<li>
			<p>Link your new stylesheet to your HTML file.</p>
			<p>Change your <code>link</code> element to look like this:</p>
			<pre><code>&lt;link rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot; href=&quot;tron_style.css&quot;&gt;</code></pre>
		</li>
		<li>Style your <code>body</code>, <code>div</code>, <code>h1</code>, and <code>p</code> tags in <code>tron_style.css</code> to make your page look like the example.</li>
	</ol>
	<p>Fun fact&mdash;you can set a different color, style, and weight on each side of an element's <code>border</code>.</p>
	<pre><code>div {
  border-top-color: blue;
  border-top-weight: 4px;

  border-left-color: red;
  border-left-weight: 1px;
}</code></pre>
</section>

